I"<p>Earlier today, a friend reached out asking to cancel our learning pod meeting. It seems that calls and other stuff took over her day, and she forgot to keep some free time to eat.</p>

<p>I replied immediately:</p>

<p><img src="/assets/no-breaks.jpg" alt="Tranquilo, let's skip the pod. We could both use a food break." /></p>

<p>For context, I‚Äôm the guy who loves free space in calendars, async work and time away from digital devices. Considering that my last few weeks are basically <em>non-stop action</em> from morning to late at night, it seems like now is a good moment to pause and ask myself gently:</p>

<p><em>WTF ARE YOU DOING, MICHA≈Å?</em></p>

<p>Checking in to my Enspiral Work Pod was a perfect opportunity to reflect on that question. Here‚Äôs what came up:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>I know very well that this is not sustainable modus operandi and I know that in the next week I will make an effort to increase the amount of free space in my day. On the other hand, I‚Äôve noticed that <strong>in order to keep up with all the open projects I‚Äôm fuelling my energy into at the moment, I needed to step up my personal productivity game, and drop some projects that I just couldn‚Äôt keep up with anymore.</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<p>In other words, the times of <em>nakurw</em> {roughly translated as ‚Äúfull fucking thrust‚Äù} forced me to cut the crap and develop a super effective way of juggling all my things to do without even noticing.</p>

<p>After all I am a juggler.</p>

<p>ü§π‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è</p>

<p>Let‚Äôs geek out on this for a bit, shall we?</p>

<h2 id="1-braindump-into-obsidian">1. Braindump into Obsidian</h2>

<pre><code>When in doubt - Braindump ‚úÖ
</code></pre>

<p>Obsidian is the central point of my digital focus. I write everything there and continuously <a href="/personal-website-flow" target="_blank">optimise it for effortlessness</a>.</p>

<p>So: I created a note called <code>Braindump ‚úÖ</code> and started dumping all the shit I want to do there.</p>

<p>It‚Äôs kinda like a backlog, but I don‚Äôt need another app for it.</p>

<p>I progressively edit the list every time I look at it, which is kinda all the time, and rearrange the order of items in order of priority. Whenever I notice resistance suggesting that a task is too big to execute, or not clear enough, I replace it with a smaller version of that task, or define it better.</p>

<p>I also added some basic guidance on top:</p>

<p><img src="/assets/braindump-note.jpg" alt="braindump note image" /></p>

<p>In this example ‚Äútax return‚Äù is way too big, and I replaced with a single step from my accounting checklist.</p>

<p>Whenever I complete a task, I move it to the <code> done ‚úÖ</code> section below all the tasks and feel the boost of endorfins kicking in.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/braindump-done.jpg" alt="done section screenshot" /></p>

<h2 id="2-timebox-in-proton-calendar">2. Timebox in Proton Calendar</h2>

<p>I timebox almost everything into my calendar, including meetings and work slots.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/calendar-full.jpg" alt="Screenshot of calendar" /></p>

<p>For work slots, I write specific tasks I intend on executing.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/calendar-details.jpg" alt="Details of work slot event" /></p>

<p>During the day I just follow the plan and dynamically adjust calendar events as needed. Whenever a task is done, I mark it as ‚úÖ.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/calendar-done.jpg" alt="Screenshot of tasks done" /></p>

<h2 id="3-reply-immediately">3. Reply Immediately</h2>

<p>I use the octopus of my digital communication channels (Signal, Telegram, Whatsapp, Email, Slack, Discord‚Ä¶) to dynamically brainstorm, schedule, and move tasks forward.</p>

<p><strong>When working with others, I aim to reply as soon as possible in order to leave the ball at their side.</strong> This way I don‚Äôt need to remember to do something - it eventually comes back to me whenever the other person is ready to bounce it back. Most people take their sweet time to reply, which is perfect because it gives me time for other tasks.</p>

<p>Of course, this is not a perfect system and I‚Äôm not perfect either, duh.</p>

<p>Sometimes I take much longer to reply, or forget to follow up on something. In any case, it works most of the times, and if a task is mission critical, it is recorded somewhere else, so I won‚Äôt forget about it completely. Worst case scenario it will take me longer to get around to it.</p>

<p>OK Computer, that‚Äôs it for the digital stuff.</p>

<p>üíª</p>

<p>Let‚Äôs zoom out for a bit into the good, old <em>organic</em> world.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/workspace-analogue-digital.jpg" alt="Digital workspace meets analogue workspace photos" /></p>

