<h2 id="4-journal-it-all">4. Journal-it-All</h2>

<p>My journal is my swiss-army-knife and One Ring to Rule Them All.</p>

<p>I journal everyday with <a href="https://infinitysquares.xyz" target="_blank">Infinity Squares</a>, as well as record tons of information, brainstorm, process, meditate and so on. Journaling is the key practice in my life, and the longest habit I kept consistently -&gt; I haven‚Äôt skipped a day since 2017, or something like that.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/journal-shelf.jpg" alt="Bookshelf with journals" /></p>

<p>While I prefer my digital tools for day-to-day tasks and calendar management, <strong>pen and paper is king for brainstorming and continuously re-aligning with my Big Dreams.</strong></p>

<p>Here‚Äôs an example of my <a href="https://journalsmarter.com/new-moon-journaling" target="_blank">Moonly Page</a> with the Squares, intentions, and important notes-to-self, which I want to see every day.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/moonly-squares-forest.jpg" alt="Moonly Spread with Infinity Squares" /></p>

<p>And here‚Äôs brainstorming / structuring a workshop to boost an Enspiral friend on her new business venture:</p>

<p><img src="/assets/journal-an-boost.jpg" alt="scan journal brainstorming page" /></p>

<h2 id="5-whiteboard">5. Whiteboard</h2>

<p>I have a whiteboard. I love whiteboards. I use it mostly to incubate ideas over a period of a few days. I write/draw stuff whenever I feel like, until incubation process is completed and I can turn an idea into reality.</p>

<p>Here‚Äôs a half-incubated participatory experience called <a href="/merging" target="_blank"><em>Merging</em></a>:</p>

<p><img src="/assets/whiteboard-merging.jpg" alt="Whiteboard" /></p>

<p>That‚Äôs it, folks.</p>

<p>Simple, fast, efficient.</p>

<p>The next step is to keep this system running while I dramatically reduce the intensity of my calendar and sink into the magical forest where I‚Äôm blessed to live.</p>

<p>Wish me luck.</p>

